data.title: Correct Process Flow
data.description: You have correctly modeled the process flow for both the Loan Applicant and the Credit Institute. The tasks are well-ordered and the sequence flows are correctly connected.

data.title: Correct Use of Gateways
data.description: You have correctly used the exclusive and parallel gateways in the Credit Institute process. The decision point for whether standard terms are applicable is well-represented by the exclusive gateway, and the parallel tasks of assessing risk and checking terms are well-represented by the parallel gateway.

data.title: Correct Use of Message Flows
data.description: You have correctly used message flows to represent the communication between the Loan Applicant and the Credit Institute. The sending of the credit request and the quote are well-represented.

data.title: Correct Use of End Events
data.description: You have correctly used end events to represent the end of both processes. This is a good practice as it clearly shows where the process ends.
